<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Lydirn Whiteheart</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-11-17 12:43:09</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>want the spoiler?<BR>
heh<BR>
Get Fiery Avenger first.<BR>
Next-<BR>
Gem of Clarity Quest in Kaladim (say 'some' around Jark in the mines- get food from his wife near cleric's guild, return it, and get gem)<BR>
Water blessed by Sacrifice (peasant woman) quest in West Freeport (say 'I will bring it' or 'I will take it') and bring the water to her brother Joshua in the building next to her<BR>
<BR>
Get tainted BP from the Plane of Hate off a Thought Corrupter (spawns after killing scorn banshee)<BR>
Get Tainted Shield from Dark Elf in Nektulos<BR>
Get Tainted sword from the Hole<BR>
<BR>
Go to Felwithe, turn in shield to Elial the pure- get Gleaming crested shield<BR>
Go to Erudin, turn in Sword and Pure Water to Reklon Ghallen, get Gleaming crested sword<BR>
Give him Tainted BP, and Gem of clarity, and get Gleaming Crested BP<BR>
Turn in all three Gleaming items, recieve mark of atonement<BR>
<BR>
go to plane of fear, wait for Irak Altil to spawn (North East corner- same pathing as our friend Cazic-thule), and give him Fiery Avenger and Mark of Atonement, recieve Fiery Defender.<BR>
<BR>
a side note, it's a very interesting story, I recommend asking Irak Altil what he is 'mumbling' about.<BR>
<BR>
True, I'm sure most of us would have liked a 1hs. But the items stats are much better than Fiery Avenger, so I hope not to hear many complaints.  The 15AC is a definate bonus.<BR>
The fact that the proc is a 155dmg stun is even better.  Stuns are what pallies are made for. Not doing damage, like our warrior counterparts.  oh, but wait...this will allow us to do somewhat decent damage AND stun!  <BR>
Neat :D<BR>
<BR>
